 Queries over the structured KG provide {\em complete answer sets} with respect to that KG. For example, if the KG contains all ACM Fellows with their countries, a simple group-by query can return a list of countries or continents with the respective numbers of fellows. One challenge is that writing structured queries can be difficult for many users. Knowledge graph question answering (KGQA) is a task that focuses on resolving natural language questions over the KG, often by applying semantic parsing to convert the user question into a structured query.